<br>
Yes as its been said time and time again our system isn't perfect but its the best thing going. This only backs that argument further. The world is filled with restrictive governing bodies, only need to look to countries that forbid women to read and the like to see that. <br>
<br>
Now for the direction I assume you were headed towards with that statement. It seems obvious the reason they did not allow foreigners to study chemistry was for fear of them using the knowledge to perform heinous acts. They perhaps went overboard with their actions denying someone access to knowledge on the principle they may misuse that information they would not be handing over anthrax to the student to do what they would with it chemistry is a major part of life and career possibilities to deny them access to it I'd hope they'd have reason to believe the person had ill intentions rather than simply because they are a foriegner. Then again perhaps if we didn't allow foreigners to take pilot lessons 9/11 would have been prevented but you can't predict everyone's intention and the what if game gets you no where if you don't have a valid reason to believe things could have been different.<br>
<br>
